wiki.summary: "Paradise" is the eighth track on Khalid’s sophomore album "Free Spirit". The song explains how Khalid and his lover’s “Free Spirit” attitude is effecting their relationship. They pray to repent from their wickedness only to fall back into their old ways. But their love will make it through the hard times. "I feel like having enough songs for people to see different sides of me as an artist. I could’ve gone forever—there were like 30 more songs. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Paradise" is the eighth track on Khalid’s sophomore album "Free Spirit". The song explains how Khalid and his lover’s “Free Spirit” attitude is effecting their relationship. They pray to repent from their wickedness only to fall back into their old ways. But their love will make it through the hard times. "I feel like having enough songs for people to see different sides of me as an artist. I could’ve gone forever—there were like 30 more songs. Although there were some that didn’t make the album, that doesn’t mean those won’t have a life. I could hit up some of my favorite artists and be like, ‘Yo, do you want to turn this into a collab and you want to hop on it?'” — Khalid for Apple Music Read more on Last.fm.
